          What types of properties sell well in St Lucia?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">St Lucia carries a mix of character Queenslanders, post-war brick homes, and modern infill. UQ precinct investment stock performs consistently for professional and post-grad rental. Character homes on larger blocks in the western streets attract families and owner-occupiers seeking the inner-west lifestyle without the inner-east price premium.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell in St Lucia?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-presented homes at accurate prices sell in 25 to 40 days. Investor stock can be quicker when yields are clearly presented to motivated buyers. Competition from Toowong and Indooroopilly listings can affect campaign length, particularly for character homes targeting family buyers.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives value in St Lucia?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">UQ proximity is a primary driver for investor stock. For owner-occupiers, value is shaped by river access on southern streets, block size, character integrity, and school catchment: Toowong State School and Brisbane State High are both meaningful catchment drivers for family buyers.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is St Lucia a good suburb to invest in?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">St Lucia has historically seen consistent rental demand from UQ post-graduate and professional tenants, with low vacancy rates underpinning investor confidence. Rental yield should be assessed against the current interest rate environment. The owner-occupier appeal of the suburb's character homes anchors resale values beyond pure yield calculations.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

